![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2c717951-9a1f-46de-ad1c-d2dce7d409df/Rey-Fenix.jpg)

Fenix has been released from his contract with All Elite Wrestling (AEW), according to a report from Fightful.

According to sources, Fenix and Penta had been in discussions with WWE in 2024, with the intention of joining the company together.

However, Fenix's contractual obligations to AEW, including a significant amount of injury time, prevented him from making the move to WWE at the time. As a result, his brother Penta, joined WWE solo.

In a development that suggests Fenix may finally be joining his brother in WWE, rumors indicate that the company has already begun working on merchandise for the incoming luchador.

This move has sparked speculation that Fenix's release from AEW may be a precursor to his WWE debut.